Package gov.nasa.gsfc.spdf.ssc

Class QueryRequest

  • java.lang.Object
    • gov.nasa.gsfc.spdf.ssc.QueryRequest
  • public class QueryRequest
extends java.lang.Object
    This class represents a request for the SSC query_server.

    Notes:

    • From a purely theoretical standpoint, this class is similar to LocatorRequest and they should probably be members of the same class heirarchy (maybe subclasses of a common base class). However, the two class were developed nearly 10 years apart using different approaches. LocatorRequest and its related classes (including BFieldModelOptions) where written by hand and then processed to be used in a SOAP interface. QueryRequest was also written by hand but it utilizes classes that were generated (using JAXB compiler) from a source XSD schema file. In order to effectively merge these classes into the same heirarchy, it would likely be necessary to redefined the SOAP interface classes by an XSD schema and regenerate them as Java classes using the JAXB compiler. But this is not likely to produce identical classes and would break compatability with SOAP clients. So for now, the two classes are independent.
    Author:
    B. Harris

        public static void validate​(gov.nasa.gsfc.sscweb.schema.QueryRequestType request,
                            java.util.Map<java.lang.String,​SpaseObservatoryDescription> satDescriptions)
                     throws SSCExternalException
        Validates the given request for correctness. Some of the validation done here could be performed by validating the XML request against its schema. If that were done, then some of the code in this method could be elminated. Other checks (for example, valid satellite identifiers) are beyond what could be specified by an XML schema.
        Parameters:
        request - client query request.
        satDescriptions - map of valid satellite descriptions.
        Throws:
        SSCExternalException - if the request is found to be invalid.
